    • Enum Constant Detail

      • WAS_OVER_MAX_NUMBER_OF_WORDS

        public static final WordSkipReason WAS_OVER_MAX_NUMBER_OF_WORDS
        Skip Reason: the Word was skipped because the WordCram had already drawn the WordCram.maxNumberOfWordsToDraw(int). It's really about the Word's rank, its position in the list once the words are sorted by weight: if its rank is greater than the value passed to maxNumberOfWordsToDraw(), then it'll be skipped, and this will be the reason code.

      • SHAPE_WAS_TOO_SMALL

        public static final WordSkipReason SHAPE_WAS_TOO_SMALL
        Skip Reason: the Word's shape was smaller than WordCram.minShapeSize(int). WordCram will only render words so small, for performance reasons. You can set the minimum Word shape size via WordCram.minShapeSize(int).

      • NO_SPACE

        public static final WordSkipReason NO_SPACE
        Skip Reason: WordCram tried placing the Word, but it couldn't find a clear spot. The WordNudger nudged it around a bunch (according to WordCram.maxAttemptsToPlaceWord(int), if it was set), but there was just no room.
